annotationA: Cyclin D, isoform D; Protein binding; protein kinase binding; cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase regulator activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cell proliferation; cellular process; mitochondrion organization; JAK-STAT cascade; regulation of cyclin-dependent protein serine/threonine kinase activity; cell growth; positive regulation of cell growth
annotationB: Regulatory particle triple-A ATPase 4 (Rpt4) is the 19S proteasomal ATPase, which is a component of the 26S proteosome complex. Rpt4 localizes to the nucleolus and participates in regulating rRNA transcription. Rpt4 physically interacts with the BHD tumor suppressor
